texts.text: >The news broadcast plays on TV.
Now on to our next story—
A protest against the income tax reform was held yesterday.
Citizens gathered en masse to voice their disapproval, and—
That bill is sure to pass. Another tax hike isn't far behind.
Protest all they want, but politicians ain't gonna listen.
What, is this law really so awful?
Do you live under a rock? It's been all over the news for days.
It's not my fault I'm not interested in politics.
Oh, wait is that the sales tax?! Then I'm soooo against it!
This is the level of awareness among today's youth, I suppose.
Well, I can't say my knowledge of politics is any better.
Now on to our next story—
Mr. Hashiba of the House of Representatives died last night.
Grief over this sudden loss has—
Didn't they announce the deaths of other Diet members recently?
Yes, Norimoto and Nobatake of the same party.
Who?
I've heard of them.
Yep, ditto.
I fear for Japan's future...
Yes, me too. Both often appeared in the media.
So, Hashiba is the third. The rumors feel more credible.
Rumors?
They've gone viral.
Since each victim was a member of the ruling party
and a strong proponent of the contested reform bill,
people have dubbed it a "cursed law" that murders all involved.
A "cursed law," eh?
Sounds like a stretch to me.
I wouldn't say that.
Oh? Whatcha mean?
Megakin, I've brought a guest.
Phew. Thanks for makin' me sweat, kid.
Bring me an iced green tea. C'mon, chop-chop.
Who's this arrogant jerkface?
Don't recognize me? I'm Aoyama, the political up-and-comer.
You're in the Diet?! You'd fit right in with the yakuza!
I know, but he really is a member of Parliament.
However, Aoyama inherited his position and has a nasty rep.
You've got some nerve to say that to my face, girlie!
And here I came all this way to request a demon exorcism.
A demon exorcism?
There is more to the sudden deaths of those representatives.
Watch this, but be warned—It's disturbing.
>Seiran plays what looks like security footage on the TV.
>It shows a single man leaving his home.
>A second later, blood gushes from a hole in his chest.
This is quite the splatter film.
Also, isn't this Mr. Hashiba who just died?
Yes. Society treated his death as untimely, but in truth...
...he was assassinated.
...That's a serious accusation.
Hold up. You mean those other MPs...
Yes, they were killed in the same fashion. Watch this.
>You look at the screen again.
>A spear-wielding man flees the scene.
Who's that?
A demon made visible with the Demon Summoning App.
...In other words, this spear demon is the culprit?
Huh, so it's not a deep fake. That sucks.
Guess I gotta take you at your word.
You're finally convinced.
In that case, will you entrust us with your father's request?
Watch it. This is MY idea.
Dad might like you, but don't push it, Little Miss Feng Shui.
But anyways, I'll give you a shot.
Listen up. Eliminate that assassin no matter what.
For whatever reason, he only targets reform bill advocates.
Protect the names on this list. Don't let anyone else die.
>Aoyama hands over a list of several Diet members.
It's a pretty short list.
Everyone else is just a worthless benchwarmer.
This is the core group, so protect them at all costs. Got it?
FYI, no one said we'd accept.
Yeah, yeah, I know. Money talks. I'll make it worth your while.
Your sugar daddy ain't got nothin' on me, sweetie.
Hey! I'm not that kinda girl, asshole!
This guy is the worst.
...Mr. Aoyama, we don't do it for the paycheck.
Our goal is to protect humanity from demons. Don't forget that.
>Megakin's tone is quiet as he glowers at the politician.
Tch. Insufferable brats.
Fine, whatever. I'll contact the Diet.
Guard 'em with your life. Got it?
Ugh, what a jerk!
Guys like him running the show means Japan is screwed.
...Megakin, can we watch that video again?
Is it somethin' about the demon?
Although brief, I saw how he wielded his spear.
His technique tells me we should proceed with caution.
He's no pushover, huh?
OK, y'all. Let's check out that footage again.
We'll divvy up guard duty afterwards, so get ready.
Hmph! Cheeky little punks.
Why should I have to count on the likes of them?
Um, pardon me. Are you Mr. Aoyama?
What? Yeah, that's me.
I knew it! I'm so happy to meet you! I'm your biggest fan!
A fan, huh?
Today's youth have a good eye.
Thank you!
Actually, there's something I'd like to discuss with you...
